goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?
goals.visualization: Violin plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A violin plot can show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data across different varieties.

goals.question: What is the trend in yield over time?
goals.visualization: Line plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: A line plot can show the trend in yield over time, allowing for analysis of any patterns or changes in yield across the two years of data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of mean yield by site
goals.rationale: A bar chart can show the mean yield for each site, allowing for comparison of the yield across different sites.

goals.question: Is there a relationship between yield and variety?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and variety, allowing for analysis of any patterns or correlations between the two variables.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
